===Amusement parks/exhibition areas/shopping/commercial centers/zoos===

====Canada====
* [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]]: [[Minirail]] (The [[Minirail]] automated [[monorail]] at [[Expo 67]], which incorporated track and rolling stock from the 1964 [[Swiss National Exhibition]])

====China====
* The [[SK (people mover)|SK people mover]] in [[Shanghai]] operates in the Bund sightseeing tunnel.

====Hong Kong====
* [[Hong Kong]]: [[Disneyland Resort Line]] (urban transit connecting to amusement park)
* [[Hong Kong]]: [[Ocean Park Hong Kong|Hong Kong Ocean Park]] [[Ocean Express]] (transit connecting the two areas of the amusement park)
* [[Hong Kong]]: [[Hong Kong International Airport Automated People Mover]] (transit connecting boarding gates with the immigration counters)

====Indonesia====
[[File:TMII Aeromovel train.JPG|thumb|Air-powered [[Aeromovel]] people mover ride around the [[Taman Mini Indonesia Indah|TMII theme park]]]]

* [[Taman Mini Indonesia Indah]] theme park [[atmospheric railway|Aeromovel]] system. However, since 2020, the aeromovel system is now defunct and all trainsets are being retrofitted with diesel engines and air conditioners, thus called Diesel Multiple Unit (DMU) and now requires a train driver to operate

====Japan====
* [[Slope car]], a small automated monorail found in various parts of Japan, can be considered as a simple form of people mover.

====United States====
* [[Anaheim]], [[California]]: The former [[PeopleMover]] attraction at [[Disneyland Park (Anaheim)|Disneyland Resort]], which ran from 1967 to 1995
* [[Bay Lake, Florida|Bay Lake]], [[Florida]]: The [[Tomorrowland Transit Authority PeopleMover]] attraction, which was formerly called the Wedway PeopleMover, in [[Tomorrowland]] at [[Magic Kingdom]] in [[Walt Disney World Resort]] which was opened in 1975
* [[Huntsville, Alabama|Huntsville]], [[Alabama]]: [[Huntsville Hospital]] [[Huntsville Hospital Tram System|People Mover]] Connects different buildings of the [[Huntsville Hospital System]].
* [[Indianapolis]], [[Indiana]]: [[Indiana University Health People Mover]] (service suspended indefinitely in February 2019)
* [[Las Colinas]], [[Irving, Texas]]: [[Las Colinas APT System]]
* [[Morgantown, West Virginia|Morgantown]], [[West Virginia]]: [[Morgantown Personal Rapid Transit]]
* [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]]: [[Mandalay Bay Tram]] In addition to the [[Las Vegas Monorail]], several people mover systems are in place in the [[Las Vegas Valley]], [[Nevada]]. Three connect the [[McCarran International Airport]] terminals 1 and 3 to its C-, D-, and E-gates. Another connects [[The Mirage]] to [[Treasure Island Hotel and Casino]]. Two people mover connects hotels on the [[Las Vegas Strip]]. The [[Mandalay Bay Tram]] connects [[Excalibur Hotel and Casino|Excalibur]], [[Luxor Hotel|Luxor]], and [[Mandalay Bay Resort and Casino|Mandalay Bay]]. The [[CityCenter#Tram|City Center Tram]] connects [[Monte Carlo Resort and Casino|Park MGM]], [[The Crystals (Las Vegas)|The Crystals]] in City Center, and the [[Bellagio (resort and casino)|Bellagio]].
* [[Orlando, Florida]]: The [[Hogwarts Express (Universal Orlando Resort)|Hogwarts Express]] attraction, a funicular railroad within [[Universal Orlando Resort]] that connects the two [[The Wizarding World of Harry Potter (Universal Orlando Resort)|The Wizarding World of Harry Potter]] sections, [[The Wizarding World of Harry Potter (Universal Orlando Resort)#Hogsmeade|Hogsmeade]] at [[Islands of Adventure]] and [[The Wizarding World of Harry Potter (Universal Orlando Resort)#Diagon Alley|Diagon Alley]] at [[Universal Studios Florida]]
* [[Reno]], [[Nevada]]: [[Circus Circus Reno]] sky shuttle operates between hotel towers in [[Reno]], [[Nevada]].&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news|last1=Potter|first1=John|title=A New Look at a Reno Classic: Downtown's Sky Shuttle|url=http://www.ktvn.com/story/19013465/a-new-look-at-a-reno-classic-downtowns-sky-shuttle|accessdate=29 March 2017|publisher=KTVN-TV|date=12 July 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170330000832/http://www.ktvn.com/story/19013465/a-new-look-at-a-reno-classic-downtowns-sky-shuttle|archivedate=30 March 2017}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* [[Washington, D.C.]]: [[United States Capitol subway system|United States Capitol Subway System]] Dirksen/Hart Line

The following are [[Monorails]] which are considered as people movers also.

* [[Anaheim, California]] - Amusement park monorail at [[Disneyland Monorail System]]
* [[Bay Lake, Florida]] - Amusement park monorail at [[Walt Disney World Monorail System]]
* [[Hershey, Pennsylvania]] - Amusement park ride monorail at [[Hersheypark]]
* [[Lancaster, Pennsylvania]] - Amusement park ride monorail at [[Dutch Wonderland]]&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web |url=http://www.dutchwonderland.com/index.asp |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2007-07-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070705061154/http://www.dutchwonderland.com/index.asp |archivedate=2007-07-05 }}&lt;/ref&gt;
* [[Ocean City, New Jersey]] - Amusement park ride monorail at [[Gillians Wonderland Pier]]
* [[Marshall, Dane County, Wisconsin|Marshall, Wisconsin]] - Amusement park ride monorail in [[Little Amerricka]]
* [[Miami, Florida]] - Zoo monorail at the [[Miami Zoo]]
* [[New York, New York]] - Zoo monorail at the [[Bronx Zoo]] 
* [[Dallas, Texas]] - Zoo monorail at the [[Dallas Zoo]]
* [[Gilroy, California]]  - [[Gilroy Gardens]] monorail provides users with an aerial view of the gardens' giant greenhouse
* [[Sacramento, California]] - California Exposition has a monorail that runs for more than a mile around their fairgrounds. It is only open during the [[California State Fair]]&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news| url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/object/article?f=/c/a/2005/08/07/TRGIKE2F4B1.DTL&amp;o=2&amp;type=printable | work=The San Francisco Chronicle | first=Spud | last=Hilton | title=The monorail at CalExpo winds more than a - Media (3 of 4) State Fair's city of fun / California's}}&lt;/ref&gt;
* [[Aiea, Hawaii]] - 	Pearlridge Center. Connects the Uptown part of the mall to the Downtown part of the mall. It is the only monorail system in Hawaii.
* [[Fairfield, Ohio]] - [[Jungle Jim's International Market]] monorail in [[Fairfield, Ohio]] brings riders from a remote parking lot to the Oscar Events Center; cars were originally used at nearby [[Kings Island]].&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web |url=http://www.kicentral.com/history/monorail.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-07-19 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081118070025/http://www.kicentral.com/history/monorail.php |archivedate=2008-11-18 }}&lt;/ref&gt;
* [[Memphis, Tennessee]] - A short suspended [[Memphis Suspension Railway|monorail]] connects [[Mud Island, Memphis|Mud Island]] in the [[Mississippi River]] to Memphis

